This problem relates to the concept of cycle parity and properties of graphs related to bipartite graphs or, more specifically, cycle bases modulo 2.

Let's analyze the condition. If all cycles have an even total weight, this means that the graph is "balanced" or, more precisely, it implies that the graph structure must satisfy certain properties regarding paths and parity.

